==English==
==={{initialism}}===
'''NSC'''

  1.) National Security Council; the comitttee in congress charged with overseeing the security of the United States, and addressing major issues of conflict and directing the course of action to be taken.  Comprised of the President, Secretary of Defense, Secretary of State heads of the major Agencies: the CIA, NSA, FBI, DHS, FIMA and the Joint Choiefs of staff from the different armed Service branches.  It usually also includes special council (advisors)to the president. 2.)  Can also refer to Natick Soldier Center (US Army).